@startuml
scale 1400 width
title VBoxManage clipboard serve - guest-to-host data event path
hide empty description
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 96

[*] --> Setup : serve starts
Setup : Get IClipboard and IHostClipboard
Setup : Register event listener
Setup --> ServeLoop
Setup --> Failed : setup error

state ServeLoop {
  [*] --> Waiting
  Waiting : Common wait state
  Waiting : waits for event, timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Stopping : timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Dispatch : event received

  Dispatch : Decode VBoxEventType
  Dispatch --> DataChangedEvent : DataChanged
  Dispatch --> TransferEvent : Transfer
  Dispatch --> OtherEvent : SourceChanged, FormatChanged,\nDataRequested, Error or ModeChanged

  DataChangedEvent : Read IClipboardItem source, MIME and buffer
  DataChangedEvent --> ValidateGuestData : source == Guest
  DataChangedEvent --> Continue : source != Guest

  ValidateGuestData : Require supported MIME type
  ValidateGuestData : Require non-empty payload
  ValidateGuestData --> PublishGuestData : valid guest-owned data
  ValidateGuestData --> Continue : unsupported or empty

  PublishGuestData : IHostClipboard::SetData(Copy, Guest, mime, bytes)
  PublishGuestData : Publish through native host endpoint
  PublishGuestData --> Continue : success
  PublishGuestData --> FailedEvent : COM error

  TransferEvent : Read transfer, state, interaction and path
  TransferEvent --> GuestFileOffer : direction == ToHost\nstate == Added or Interaction
  TransferEvent --> TransferProgress : direction == ToHost\nstate update
  TransferEvent --> Continue : direction != ToHost

  GuestFileOffer : IClipboardTransfer::Roots/List/Query
  GuestFileOffer : approve() or deny(reason)
  GuestFileOffer : respond() for overwrite, rename,\ndestination or recovery
  GuestFileOffer --> Continue : approved, denied or pending

  TransferProgress : Track InProgress, Completed,\nCanceled, Failed or Removed
  TransferProgress --> Continue

  OtherEvent : Handled by another focused diagram
  OtherEvent --> Continue

  Continue --> Waiting
  FailedEvent : Print serve failure
  FailedEvent --> Stopping
}

ServeLoop --> Cleanup : stopped
Failed --> Cleanup
Cleanup : IHostClipboard::Clear()
Cleanup : Unregister listener
Cleanup : Uninstall signal handler
Cleanup --> [*]

note right of PublishGuestData
  Main SetData path:
  - accepts only ClipboardSource_Guest
  - checks shared clipboard mode and payload size
  - maps MIME to Shared Clipboard protocol format
  - converts the payload to protocol bytes
  - calls GuestShCl::reportFormatsToHost()
  - calls GuestShCl::writeDataToHost()

  Generic Main clipboard cache/source is preserved,
  preventing a guest-to-host publication from being
  reflected back as host-owned clipboard state.
end note

note right of GuestFileOffer
  Guest-to-host file offers are represented by
  IClipboardTransfer(ToHost). The host client inspects
  transfer roots and metadata. getSourcePaths() may be
  empty here because the producer-side files are in the
  guest or are virtual, not host-local source paths.
  Main/native host clipboard automation then materializes
  requested transfer-relative objects.
end note

@enduml
' EOF
